## Performance

Kreuzberg is built on a Rust core for native performance. Typical extraction speeds:

- **PDF (text-based)**: 10-100 MB/s
- **Images (with OCR)**: 1-5 MB/s (backend dependent)
- **Office documents**: 20-200 MB/s

See [Benchmarks](https://kreuzberg.dev/benchmarks/) for detailed performance metrics.

## Supported Formats

Kreuzberg supports **56+ file formats** including:

**Documents**: PDF, DOCX, DOC, XLSX, XLS, PPTX, PPT, ODS, ODT, ODP

**Archives**: ZIP, TAR, GZIP, 7Z, RAR

**Web**: HTML, XML, JSON, YAML, TOML

**Images**: PNG, JPG, GIF, BMP, TIFF, WebP

**Other**: EML, MSG, TXT, Markdown, RTF, CSV, and more

Full list at [Supported Formats](https://kreuzberg.dev/formats/).

